&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;About Lucid&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;At Lucid, we are creating exceptional mobility experiences through innovation to drive the world forward. Built on Lucid’s proprietary technology and software-defined vehicle architecture, our award-winning vehicles bring our “Compromise Nothing™” approach to the global automotive market. That means refusing to choose between performance and sustainability, design and engineering, ambition and integrity. In Lucid Air and Lucid Gravity, we have designed and built vehicles that have redefined their segments, combining exceptional range, performance, design, and expansive space in a single experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:210,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:210,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:300}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;We achieve this through deep vertical integration, with design, engineering, and production&amp;nbsp;happening in-house&amp;nbsp;across our global offices and&amp;nbsp;manufacturing&amp;nbsp;facilities.&amp;nbsp;Our&amp;nbsp;teams&amp;nbsp;come&amp;nbsp;from&amp;nbsp;industries&amp;nbsp;around the world, united by a shared commitment to excellence.&amp;nbsp;By refusing to settle, you&amp;nbsp;can&amp;nbsp;help&amp;nbsp;redefine&amp;nbsp;what’s&amp;nbsp;possible and&amp;nbsp;shape the future of mobility.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Lucid Motors is seeking a highly motivated 5-Axis Machinist, Vehicle Integration with an understanding of fundamental shop knowledge. This position will report to the Maintenance Manager. The ideal candidate is extremely hands-on with solid experience in CNC machining.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You Will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work from solid models, technical drawings, engineering sketches, and other such documentation to produce a variety of prototype and production parts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze written specifications, drawings, rough sketches, and verbal instructions to determine operation sequences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with tolerances of +/- .10 mm in most cases with less frequent requirements of +/-.01 mm.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience programming live multi-axis machining, not just 3+2.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand and implement high level multi-axis machining techniques as well as HSM/HEM methods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a tidy and safe work environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain supportive, professional relationships with technicians, designers and engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You Bring:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma or GED required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Machinist Apprenticeship or 4+ years’ experience as a Machinist required, Bachelor’s degree or equivalent is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work flexible schedule, overtime, and weekends when necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in Stamping and/or complex manufacturing preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated problem solving and troubleshooting experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High degree of proficiency with HyperMill, NX, Tebis or WorkNC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-depth knowledge of G/M code along with parametric programming, macros and post processor syntax&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand all aspects of machine setup and operation including tool setup&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to machine parts to specification working from CAD files, mechanical drawings and sketches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read, understand, and create technical mechanical drawings, including orthographic projections, sectional views, part notes and di

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;About Lucid&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;At Lucid, we are creating exceptional mobility experiences through innovation to drive the world forward. Built on Lucid’s proprietary technology and software-defined vehicle architecture, our award-winning vehicles bring our “Compromise Nothing™” approach to the global automotive market. That means refusing to choose between performance and sustainability, design and engineering, ambition and integrity. In Lucid Air and Lucid Gravity, we have designed and built vehicles that have redefined their segments, combining exceptional range, performance, design, and expansive space in a single experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:210,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:210,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:300}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;We achieve this through deep vertical integration, with design, engineering, and production&amp;nbsp;happening in-house&amp;nbsp;across our global offices and&amp;nbsp;manufacturing&amp;nbsp;facilities.&amp;nbsp;Our&amp;nbsp;teams&amp;nbsp;come&amp;nbsp;from&amp;nbsp;industries&amp;nbsp;around the world, united by a shared commitment to excellence.&amp;nbsp;By refusing to settle, you&amp;nbsp;can&amp;nbsp;help&amp;nbsp;redefine&amp;nbsp;what’s&amp;nbsp;possible and&amp;nbsp;shape the future of mobility.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Lucid Motors, we’re building the future of mobility and our Finance &amp;amp; Accounting team plays a key role in supporting that growth across Europe. We’re looking for an enthusiastic &lt;strong&gt;Accounting Intern&lt;/strong&gt; to join our European Finance Team. This is a great opportunity for a student who wants to kick-start a career in accounting and gain hands-on experience in a fast-paced, international environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will report directly to the Accounting Lead and contribute to day-to-day operations as well as month-end activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Accounting Intern, you will support the team with both recurring activities and improvement initiatives, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist the Accounting Team with daily tasks and month-end close activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help prepare, review, and post journal entries under guidance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the team in preparing for local statutory filings and audit-related requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help maintain accurate documentation and assist with basic reconciliations (as needed)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to projects that improve accounting and finance processes, tools, and ways of working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we’re looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who is eager to learn, structured, and comfortable working with numbers and detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently enrolled in a Bachelor’s or Master’s program (HBO/WO) in Accounting, Finance, Economics, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent in English (written and spoken)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills and comfortable working with different stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail-oriented, well-organized, and reliable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving mindset and ability to learn quickly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous internship, part-time job, or coursework relevant to accounting/finance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic familiarity with accounting concept

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;About Lucid&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;At Lucid, we are creating exceptional mobility experiences through innovation to drive the world forward. Built on Lucid’s proprietary technology and software-defined vehicle architecture, our award-winning vehicles bring our “Compromise Nothing™” approach to the global automotive market. That means refusing to choose between performance and sustainability, design and engineering, ambition and integrity. In Lucid Air and Lucid Gravity, we have designed and built vehicles that have redefined their segments, combining exceptional range, performance, design, and expansive space in a single experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:210,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:210,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:300}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
